    "body": "> > ```\r\n> >  Here are the timings of modules in your prompt (>=1ms or output):\r\n> >  directory  -  <1ms  -   \"~ \"\r\n> > ```\r\n> > \r\n> > \r\n> >     \r\n> >       \r\n> >     \r\n> > \r\n> >       \r\n> >     \r\n> > \r\n> >     \r\n> >   \r\n> > though this delay is not just with ~ instead its more with starting terminal with starship at any dir\r\n> \r\n> Right you use zsh right? Could you give your .zshrc file? Cuz loading profiles and stuff take time it's not a problem with starship. At least up to my knowledge\r\n\r\nnot sure how this is a .zshrc issue as it remains constant for both p10k and starship, but sure here's my [zshrc](https://github.com/karshPrime/dotfiles/blob/main/config/zsh/zshrc)",
