    "body": "> Ok: p10k does some async stuff, but that should affect git operations in big repos and similar stuff to be really that noticeable. This feels like the general startup of your shell is slow. If this is starship, you could try to \"prerender\" the init script and source that instead of sourcing the starship init call (just dump that output into a file and source it directly instead of getting it from the starship init call).\r\n\r\nwhat am i not getting right?\r\n![image](https://github.com/starship/starship/assets/94996251/bbbefe8d-b8af-46a9-acf1-087f6d2b033f)\r\n",
